        "speakerNotes": "Welcome to OSA. This presentation covers what we built, how it works, where we are, and where we're headed."
      },
      {
        "id": "problem",
        "layout": "single-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## The Problem",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "Researchers work with **specialized open science tools** (HED, BIDS, EEGLAB, MNE)",
                "children": [
                  "Each tool has its own docs, forums, mailing lists, GitHub repos",
                  "Knowledge is scattered across 20+ year archives"
                ]
              },
              "General-purpose AI assistants **hallucinate domain-specific answers**",
              "Small communities (dozens to hundreds of users) can't justify building custom AI tools",
              "Researchers need **precise, citation-backed answers**, not creative guesses"
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 0 },
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "fade", "index": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "The core tension: researchers need precise help with specific tools, but their communities are too small to build custom AI solutions. General AI hallucinates tool-specific answers."
      },
      {
        "id": "principles",
        "layout": "two-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Design Principles",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "**Precision over features**",
                "children": ["Citation-backed answers", "Anti-hallucination by design"]
              },
              {
                "text": "**Simple infrastructure**",
                "children": ["Lab server deployment", "No Kubernetes, no vector DB"]
              }
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "left", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "**Extensible tools**",
                "children": ["YAML-driven community configs", "Plugin system for custom tools"]
              },
              {
                "text": "**Domain expertise**",
                "children": ["Deep knowledge of specific tools", "Not a broad generalist"]
              }
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "right", "order": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "These four principles guide every decision. We deliberately chose NOT to build for enterprise scale, millions of users, or complex multi-tenant scenarios."
      },
      {
        "id": "architecture",
        "layout": "single-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Architecture",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "**User** --> **Cloudflare Worker** --> **FastAPI Backend** --> **Community Registry**",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large", "alignment": "center", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "headers": ["Layer", "Component", "Role"],
            "rows": [
              ["Edge", "Cloudflare Worker", "CORS, rate limiting, bot protection"],
              ["API", "FastAPI + LangGraph", "Agent orchestration, tool calling"],
              ["Registry", "YAML configs", "Auto-discovers community assistants"],
              ["Assistants", "HED, BIDS, EEGLAB, MNE, ...", "Domain-specific agents with tools"],
              ["Knowledge", "SQLite + FTS5", "Per-community databases, BM25 search"]
            ],
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 1 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "Simple single-instance architecture. Cloudflare Worker handles CORS, rate limiting, bot protection. FastAPI backend with LangGraph agents. Each community gets its own assistant with auto-generated tools. SQLite with FTS5 for knowledge search."
      },
      {
        "id": "tech-stack",
        "layout": "single-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Tech Stack",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "headers": ["Component", "Technology", "Why"],
            "rows": [
              ["Agent Orchestration", "LangGraph", "State machine for tool-calling loops"],
              ["API Server", "FastAPI", "Async, auto-docs, type-safe"],
              ["LLM Access", "LiteLLM + OpenRouter", "Unified provider interface, BYOK"],
              ["Knowledge Store", "SQLite + FTS5", "Zero-config, per-community DBs"],
              ["Edge Proxy", "Cloudflare Worker", "Global CDN, bot protection, CORS"],
              ["Frontend", "Embeddable JS Widget", "Drop-in for any website"],
              ["Observability", "LangFuse", "Token tracking, session replay"],
              ["CLI", "Typer + Rich", "Thin HTTP client, ~7 deps"]
            ],
            "caption": "Deliberately simple choices for lab-scale deployment",
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "Every tech choice optimizes for simplicity. SQLite over Postgres, in-memory state over Redis, direct doc fetching over vector DBs. A single Docker container runs everything."
      },
      {
        "id": "yaml-onboarding",
        "layout": "two-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Community Onboarding",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "### One YAML file = One community\nNo Python required for basic setup.\nAuto-discovered at startup, no code changes needed.",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large", "alignment": "left" },
            "position": { "area": "left", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "code": "id: my-community\nname: My Research Tool\nstatus: available\ndefault_model: anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5\n\ndocumentation:\n  - title: User Guide\n    preload: true\n    source_url: https://raw.github...\n\ngithub:\n  repos:\n    - org/my-tool\n\nsync:\n  github:\n    cron: \"0 2 * * *\"\n\nwidget:\n  title: My Tool Assistant\n  suggested_questions:\n    - How do I get started?",
            "language": "python",
            "caption": "src/assistants/my-community/config.yaml",
            "lineNumbers": false,
            "position": { "area": "right", "order": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "The YAML config is the core innovation for onboarding. A single file defines identity, docs, GitHub sync, knowledge sources, widget behavior, and budget limits. Auto-discovery at startup means no code changes needed."
      },
      {
        "id": "what-yaml-drives",
        "layout": "single-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## What the YAML Drives",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "headers": ["config.yaml drives...", "What gets generated"],
            "rows": [
              ["API Routes", "POST /community/ask, POST /community/chat"],
              ["System Prompt", "Preloaded docs, tool descriptions, persona"],
              ["Knowledge Tools", "search_discussions, search_papers, retrieve_docs"],
              ["Sync Schedules", "GitHub nightly, papers weekly, docstrings weekly"],
              ["Widget", "Title, suggested questions, branding, theme"],
              ["Budget", "Daily and monthly spending limits per community"]
            ],
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "One YAML file generates API routes, system prompt, knowledge tools, sync schedules, widget configuration, and budget limits. All auto-discovered at startup."
      },
