        "speakerNotes": "Six research communities live, each with tailored knowledge and tools. HED was first, then rapid onboarding of the others using the YAML registry system."
      },
      {
        "id": "tool-system",
        "layout": "two-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Tool System",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "**Auto-generated from YAML**",
                "children": [
                  "retrieve_{id}_docs",
                  "search_{id}_discussions",
                  "search_{id}_papers",
                  "search_{id}_code_docs",
                  "search_{id}_faq"
                ]
              }
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "left", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "**Custom Python plugins**",
                "children": [
                  "HED: validate_hed_string, suggest_hed_tags",
                  "NEMAR: search_nemar_datasets",
                  "Any @tool decorated function"
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "**Knowledge sources**",
                "children": [
                  "GitHub issues and PRs",
                  "Academic papers via OpenALEX",
                  "Mailing list archives",
                  "Discourse forums",
                  "Code docstrings"
                ]
              }
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "right", "order": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "Two-tier tool system: auto-generated knowledge tools from YAML config, plus custom Python plugins for domain-specific functionality like HED validation."
      },
      {
        "id": "knowledge-pipeline",
        "layout": "single-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Knowledge Pipeline",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "**Sources** --> **Nightly Sync** --> **SQLite FTS5** --> **BM25 Ranking** --> **Cited Response**",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large", "alignment": "center", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "**5 knowledge sources synced automatically**",
                "children": [
                  "GitHub issues and PRs (nightly)",
                  "Academic papers via OpenALEX (weekly)",
                  "Mailing list archives (EEGLAB: 20+ years)",
                  "Discourse forums (MNE, FieldTrip)",
                  "Code docstrings from MATLAB and Python repos"
                ]
              }
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 1 }
          },
          {
            "type": "callout",
            "calloutType": "important",
            "content": "Knowledge is for **discovery only**. The assistant links users to relevant discussions rather than answering from them.",
            "position": { "area": "footer", "order": 0 },
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "fade", "index": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "Multiple knowledge sources synced on schedules into per-community SQLite databases. FTS5 provides fast keyword + BM25 search. Key design choice: knowledge is for discovery and citation, not for generating answers from."
      },
      {
        "id": "faq-pipeline",
        "layout": "single-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Smart FAQ Generation",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "**Stage 1: Evaluation** (cheap model, Qwen3-235B FP8)",
                "children": [
                  "Score each mailing list thread for quality",
                  "Threads below 0.7 threshold are skipped (~85% of threads)"
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "**Stage 2: Summarization** (quality model, Claude Haiku 4.5)",
                "children": [
                  "Only high-scoring threads get summarized",
                  "Generates structured FAQ entries with citations"
                ]
              }
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "callout",
            "calloutType": "tip",
            "content": "Two-stage pipeline reduces summary costs by **~85%**. EEGLAB: 20+ years of mailing list archives processed.",
            "position": { "area": "footer", "order": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "Cost-efficient FAQ generation: cheap eval model scores thread quality first, quality summary model only processes high-scoring threads. Reduced EEGLAB processing costs by ~85%."
      },
      {
        "id": "widget",
        "layout": "two-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Embeddable Widget",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              "**Drop-in** JS snippet for any website",
              "**Page-aware**: shares current URL and title as context",
              "**BYOK**: users bring their own API key",
              "Chat history in localStorage",
              "Markdown rendering with code copy",
              "Resizable and pop-out window",
              "Cloudflare Turnstile bot protection",
              "Community logos and branding"
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "left", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "code": "<script\n  src=\"https://demo.osc.earth/widget.js\"\n  data-community=\"hed\">\n</script>",
            "language": "html",
            "caption": "Minimal integration: one script tag",
            "lineNumbers": false,
            "position": { "area": "right", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "Live at **demo.osc.earth** -- auto-populates community cards from API",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large", "alignment": "center", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "footer", "order": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "The widget is designed for easy embedding. Page context awareness means it knows what documentation page the user is reading. Demo page auto-discovers communities from the API."
      },
      {
        "id": "current-state",
        "layout": "two-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Where We Are (v0.7.1)",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "callout",
            "calloutType": "tip",
            "title": "Working Well",
            "content": "6 communities live and serving\nYAML-driven onboarding proven\nKnowledge sync running nightly\nWidget deployed on community sites\nCLI available via pip install\nPrompt caching reducing costs\n~$1-5/mo for 10K requests",
            "position": { "area": "left", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "callout",
            "calloutType": "warning",
            "title": "Known Gaps",
            "content": "Ephemeral preview backends (not yet designed)\nCross-community delegation (planned)\nSession persistence across restarts\nSecurity hardening (SSRF, key redaction)\nAudio/video material support",
            "position": { "area": "right", "order": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "Honest assessment. The platform works well for its current scope. The ephemeral backend is the biggest design gap; it will take significant work to design and implement, but it is critical for enabling community maintainers to develop and test their configs independently."
      },
      {
        "id": "agent-arena",
        "layout": "single-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Future: Multi-Assistant Delegation",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "**User** asks HED Assistant about data format --> HED **delegates to BIDS** --> response with attribution",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large", "alignment": "center", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              "Assistants **delegate to peer specialists** when questions cross domains",
              "Peers declared explicitly in config, no surprise routing",
              "Depth limit of 1, no delegation chains",
              "Attribution: *According to the BIDS assistant...*",
              "Future: universal /ask endpoint with auto-routing"
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 1 },
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "fade", "index": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "The agent arena vision: community assistants that can delegate to each other. A HED user asking about BIDS data organization gets routed to the BIDS specialist. Explicit peer declaration keeps it predictable."
      },
      {
        "id": "ephemeral-backends",
        "layout": "single-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Future: Ephemeral Preview Backends",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "**Goal**: Community maintainers develop and test configs without touching production",
                "children": [
                  "Push to feature branch triggers CI build",
                  "Docker image deployed on a new port automatically",
                  "Full working preview URL provided",
                  "Community maintainers test their YAML changes end-to-end"
                ]
              }
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "callout",
            "calloutType": "warning",
            "title": "Status",
            "content": "Not yet designed. Significant infrastructure work needed for port allocation, resource cleanup, and database isolation. This is the key to making OSA truly self-service.",
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 1 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "The ephemeral backend is the biggest design challenge ahead. It needs careful architecture to handle port allocation, resource cleanup, and database isolation. But it is the key to making OSA truly self-service for community maintainers."
      },
