      },
      {
        "id": "why-it-matters",
        "layout": "single-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Why It Matters",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xxl", "alignment": "left", "color": "#1D4ED8" },
            "position": { "area": "header", "order": 0 }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "**For researchers**",
                "children": [
                  "Precise, domain-specific help instead of generic AI hallucinations",
                  "Answers backed by real issues, papers, and documentation",
                  "Embedded where they already work (project websites, docs)"
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "**For community maintainers**",
                "children": [
                  "One YAML file to create an AI assistant for their tool",
                  "No ML expertise required",
                  "Automated knowledge sync keeps it current"
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "**For the ecosystem**",
                "children": [
                  "Shared infrastructure across small communities",
                  "Cross-community knowledge flow via delegation",
                  "Open source, lab-deployable, cost-effective at ~$1-5/mo"
                ]
              }
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 0 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "The value proposition at three levels: individual researchers get better help, maintainers get an easy way to serve their community, and the ecosystem benefits from shared infrastructure and cross-pollination."
      },
      {
        "id": "closing",
        "layout": "title",
        "background": "#F0F4FF",
